The paper deals with an online learning problem, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The problem involves choosing a distribution from a set of feasible distributions, which can be viewed as an information-theoretic problem and thus falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the problem in the context of convex optimization, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of regularizers in the Dual Averaging method suggests a connection to regularization techniques in machine learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses regret bounds, which is a topic in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
